Finally, the desired volume is \[\frac{1}{3}r^2h\pi = \frac{1}{3}(15^2)(3\sqrt{11})\pi = {225\pi\sqrt{11}}.\]So, dividing the volume by $\pi$ gives $\boxed{225\sqrt{11}}$.

